body:
After updating to next `15.3.0` I'm seeing that locally imported fonts still work (I'm using Tailwind):

```
@layer base {
  @font-face {
    font-family: 'MT Baskerville ET W08 Italic';
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-display: swap;
    src:
      local('MT Baskerville ET W08 Italic'),
      url('/fonts/MT Baskerville ET W08 Italic/MT Baskerville ET W08 Italic.ttf')
        format('truetype');
  }
...
```

but not Google fonts loaded from a remote url:
```
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Oswald:300,300i,700,800')
```

When I downloaded the Google font and imported it locally, everything is back to normal
